An interactive AI-powered application that allows users to upload PDF documents and ask questions in natural language. The system uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to ensure responses are grounded in the uploaded document.

Features
📂 Upload PDF documents
💬 Ask questions in natural language
🧠 AI-generated answers using OpenAI LLM
🔎 Context-aware retrieval (RAG)
📑 Source page references
⚡ Fast vector search using ChromaDB
🌐 Simple UI built with Gradio

![ChatWithPDF Screenshot](https://s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/ivanchiu.info/asset/chatWithPDF.png)


How it Works 

1) PDF Handling 

Load PDF using PyPDFLoader
Split text into smaller chunks
Convert chunks into embeddings via OpenAI
Store embeddings in Chroma vector database

PDF → Text → Chunks → Embeddings → Vector DB

2) Prompt Handling (RAG)

Convert user question into embedding
Retrieve most relevant chunks from vector DB
Build prompt with:
      Context (retrieved chunks)
      User question
Generate answer using OpenAI LLM

Question → Embedding → Retrieve → Prompt → Answer

3) Remark : API and virtual (Windows CMD)

.venv\Scripts\activate
set OPENAI_API_KEY="XXXXXXXX"
python app.py
http://127.0.0.1:7860

4) Run

go to http://127.0.0.1:7860
Upload a PDF file
Wait for processing (embedding + indexing)
Ask questions in the chat box
Get AI-generated answers based on the document

